result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (3rd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Bennie Alonzo Teague was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine of $700.00 PLUS all mandatory costs, fees and surcharges to be paid by 11/09/17 or serve 30 days in the House of Correction.
Court ordered defendant's operating privileges revoked for 18 months with the mandatory reinstatement fee.

Defendant's operating privilege for operation of Class D vehicles is restricted to operating vehicles that are equipped with an ignition interlock device; and each motor vehicle for which the defendant's name appears on the vehicle's certificate of title or registration must be equipped with an ignition interlock device beginning on the date the department issues any license and for a period of  two years  thereafter.
AODA assessment and follow through with recommended programming.
Concurrent with: concurrent to any other sentence with credit for 6 days time served.  Huber privileges pursuant to Sec. 303.08 Wis. Stats to apply for work. Sentence to commence forthwith.

Defendant Bennie Alonzo Teague in court with attorney Jason Canfield.  Alyssa M. Schaller appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 

 AS TO COUNT ONE: 
 Defendant waived rights and pled guilty.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire received and filed.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Parties stipulate to the facts of the complaint as a basis for a guilty plea.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the complaint.  Judgment of Conviction entered. 

ON MOTION OF THE STATE, COURT ORDERED COUNTS TWO AND THREE:  DISMISSED. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

The Court ordered the Defendant to serve six months in the House of Correction, concurrent  to any other sentence with credit for 6 days time served.  Huber privileges pursuant to Sec. 303.08 Wis. Stats to apply for work. Sentence to commence forthwith. 

Fine of $700.00 PLUS all mandatory  costs, fees and surcharges  to be paid by 11/09/ 17 or serve 30 days  in the House of Correction.

Court ordered defendant's operating privileges revoked for  18  months with the mandatory reinstatement fee.

AODA assessment and follow through with recommended programming. 

Defendant's operating privilege for operation of Class D vehicles is restricted to operating vehicles that are equipped with an ignition interlock device; and each motor vehicle for which the defendant's name appears on the vehicle's certificate of title or registration must be equipped with an ignition interlock device beginning on the date the department issues any license and for a period of  two years  thereafter.
